--> Javascript is : 
  
             . High-level
             . Garbage collected
             . interpretted or just-in-time compiled
             . multi- paradigm
             . Prototype-based object oriented
             . First-class functions
             . Dynamic
             . Single-threaded
             . Non-Blocking event loop
             
             
--> Javascript Engine :  Any javascript engine contains of a callstack and Heap.
                        . Callstack is actually where our code get executed.
                        . The heap is the unstructured pool which holds all the object that our application needs.
                        
              Q- How the code is compiled to machine code ?
              A-  first parsing then compilation and then ececution.
              
